Strike Rate- the strike rate for a [[batter]] is the 'average' of his runs. This is usally shown by the number of runs divided by the number of balls faced by the individual. But on rare occasions it has been known to be the number of runs divided by the minuites on strike.

Usaly this is shown as a decimal eg. 1.4 for the average of 1.4 runs off every ball faced. 
But can also be a percentage 1.4 is then 140%. Using strike rate can quickly help individuals see who is preforming well with the bat, and also who has 'dug in'.